    "for both language pairs using LLM-based classification.",
    "Panel A reports findings for Python versus R. For function addition analysis in low-activity projects, commits with new function definitions increase by 0.276 per quarter, while commits without new function definitions increase by 1.915 per quarter-a difference of 1.639 commits.",
    "For high-activity projects, the coefficients on the triple interaction terms reveal substantially larger effects: an additional 0.902 increase for function-adding commits and an additional 7.942 increase for non-function-adding commits.",
